6. Algorithm / Methodology
FIFO Algorithm
•	Pages are replaced in the order they entered memory.
•	The oldest page is removed first.
LRU Algorithm
•	Replaces the page that has not been used for the longest time.
•	Tracks last access time of each page.
Optimal Algorithm
•	Replaces the page that will not be used for the longest time in the future.
•	Requires future reference knowledge.
General Steps
1.	Initialize all frames as empty
2.	For each page request:
o	Check for HIT or FAULT
o	If FAULT and frames are full:
	Apply replacement algorithm
3.	Count page faults
4.	Display results
 
