8. Conclusion & Future Scope
Conclusion
This project successfully demonstrates the working of FIFO, LRU, and Optimal page replacement algorithms. By simulating page requests and memory frames, the project helps in understanding how operating systems manage memory and minimize page faults.
The comparison clearly shows that:
•	FIFO is simple but inefficient
•	LRU performs better with locality of reference
•	Optimal gives the minimum possible page faults
